Class PanaceaSDK

java.lang.Object
  com.panacea.sdk.PanaceaSDK

public class PanaceaSDK
extends java.lang.Object

Point of initialization for user of the SDK. All interaction with the Panacea SDK should be done through this object

registerDevice

public void registerDevice()
The first web call done in the registration process. This method takes care of GCM registration automatically - if the GCM key has changed the Panacea server will be notified. Then determines if the device needs to be registered or only checked for verification.

registerPhoneNumber

public void registerPhoneNumber(java.lang.String phoneNumber)
                         throws PMInvalidPhoneNumberException
If the notification returned by registerDevice() is PanaceaSDK.Result.REQUEST_PHONE_NUMBER the user should be prompted for phone number then this method should be called with the number. format should be international format with +country code

Parameters:
phoneNumber - String in international format with +country code
Throws:
PMInvalidPhoneNumberException - if the phone number does not pass validation

registerVerification

public void registerVerification(java.lang.String verificationCode)
If the notification returned by registerPhoneNumber(java.lang.String) is PanaceaSDK.Result.REQUEST_VERIFICATION_CODE the user should be prompted for the verification code this method should be called with the code.

Parameters:
verificationCode - sent via SMS (text)
